HEADWORD: Implacentalia
<hw>Im`pla*cen*ta"li*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>In-</er> not, and <er>Placental</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A primary division of the Mammalia, including
the monotremes and marsupials, in which no placenta is formed.</def>⟦br⟧
